ory-no-grade-items-included.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(63,1,'2012-08-23 12:03:31','2012-08-23 12:03:31','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world-2','','','2012-08-23 12:03:31','2012-08-23 12:03:31','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?p=1',0,'post','',0),(64,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:05','2012-08-23 12:18:05','<div class=\"section\">              <p>Create grade items and categories in the Manage Grades Area.</p>      <p><strong>Grade Items</strong> are mandatory items for your gradebook. They correspnd to an item in your evaluation plan such as \'Mid term exam.\'</p>      <p>Use<strong> Grade Categories</strong>  to organize your grade items and to make distribution of similar grades easier. For example, you may have five assignments, A1 through A5, under a category called \'Assignments.\' This makes it easy to distribute marks and drop assignments with the highest or lowest grade. Categories are not required. </p>  <p>The grades tool uses the value you give to grade items and grade categories to calculate final grades. Grade items that are in a category must sum to 100. Individual grade items and categories must also sum to 100. Otherwise, the Final Calculated Grade calculation will be inaccurate.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/initial-manage-grades.png\"/><h3>Create grade items</h3>                <p><strong>STEP 1</strong></p>          <p>Choose the type of grade item that you want to create.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new-grade-item-options.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 2</strong></p>          <div>                  <p>Set the <strong>Properties</strong> of the grade item.</p>                  <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new-grade-item-properties.png\"/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><p>The name of your grade item should match the name of the same item in your evaluation plan. The short name may make your gradebook easier to view.Students will not see the sort name.</p>                  <p>If there are several related items, you can place them in a category. This is optional.</p>                  <br/><br/><br/><br/><p><strong>Max. Points</strong> = the number of point that the grade item will be graded out of.</p>                  <p><strong>Weight</strong> = the amount (%) that you want the grade item to contribute to the category or final grade. If a grade item is in a category, the weight contributes to the category, not the final grade.</p><p>                     <br clear=\"all\"/></p></div>    <h3>Optionally, create grade categories</h3>                <p>The image below shows a gradebook with individual grade items only. Note that the sum of the weights of these five grade items is 100.</p>          <p>A1, A2, and A3 represent assignments. If the evaluation plan requires that you drop the users\' lowest assignment grade before calculating their final grade, you should create a category for the assignments.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new-grade-category.png\"/><p>Set the <strong>Properties</strong> of the grade item.</p>          <div>                  <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new-grade-category-properties.png\"/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><p>Category weight is 30. The sum of the weights of all items in the category must be 30.</p>                  <p>Distribution options determine how items are handled within the category. In this case, the lowest item will be droped and the remaing items will be weighted evenly (15% of the category each).</p>           <br clear=\"all\"/></div>           <p>When you go back to <strong>Manage Grades</strong> you will see that the assignments are not part of the category. You will also see a warning at the top.</p>           <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new-grade-category-no-grade-items-included.png\"/><div>               <p>You can edit each grade item in order to associate them item with the category.</p>               <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/assign-grade-item-to-category.png\"/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><p>When you choose the category from the dropdown list, the <strong>weight</strong> of the item will adjust automatically. So far, only A1 is part of the category so its weight is 100% of the category. When you add a grade items, A2 and A3, the gradebook will assign 33.3333% to each grade item in the category for a total of 100%.</p>          <br clear=\"all\"/></div>          <p>Below is the gradebook with the \'Assignments\' category.</p>          <p><strong>NOTES:</strong></p>          <ol><li>The Assignments category, and the Midterm and Final grade items, sum to 100% for the gradebook.</li>              <li>A1, A2, and A3 must sum to 100% for the category.</li>              <li>The gradebook is set up to drop the assignment with the lowest grade. The weights of the remaining items will adjust from 33.33% to 50%.</li>              <li>The Final grade item is hidden from students (see the \'eye\' icon). The last item in the gradebook should always be hidden from students.</li>          </ol><img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/category-with-items.png\"/></div>','Create grade items and categories','Array','publish','closed','closed','','create-grade-items-and-categories','','','2012-08-23 12:42:25','2012-08-23 12:42:25','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?page_id=9',1,'guides','',0),(65,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:15','2012-08-23 12:18:15','<div class=\"section\">               <p>When the gradebook is set up the way you want it for your course, it is easy to enter, import, and export student grades. The names of students enrolled in the course will be in the gradebook. Enter the grades for each student in the appropriate cells.</p>       <p><strong>Steps to enter grades and calculate the \'Final Calculated Grade\'</strong>       </p><ol><li>In the Grades tool, click <strong> Enter Grades</strong></li>          <li>Make sure you are in Spreadsheet View - you can enter grades in each cell</li>          <li>When you click <strong>Save</strong> the gradebook will calculate the \'Final Calculated Grade\' using the grades that are in the cells and the grading system that you are using. The \'Final Calculated Grade\' will be incomplete until all grades have been entered.</li>        </ol><img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/enter-grades.png\"/><p><strong>Student view of their grades in Desire2Learn</strong></p>       <div>       <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/student-view-of-grades.png\"/><ol><br/><li>Students will see thier grades only</li>          <li>Students do not see the \'Final Exam\' grade item because the last item in the gradebook is hidden</li>          <li>Final grades are released via Memorial Self-Service</li>        </ol><br clear=\"all\"/></div><p><strong>Steps to enter garades into the \'Final Adjusted Grade\' column</strong>       </p><p>You can transfer grades into the \'Final Adjusted Grade\' column and make manual adjustments as needed. Grades must be in the \'Final Adjusted Grade\' column in order for them to be transferred to Banner.</p>       <p>You can transfer grades one student at a time by clicking on a student\'s name in the gradebook. You will go to the following screen:.</p>       <div>        <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/transfer-grades-by-student-V2.png\"/><ol><br/><br/><br/><li>Click on the green arrow to enter the student\'s grade in the \'Final Adjusted Grade cell\'. You can enter a grade manually if you want a student\'s grade to be different from the calculated final grade.</li>          <li>Go to the next student by clicking the \'User Details\' arrows.</li>        </ol><br clear=\"all\"/></div>       <p>You can transfer the grades for all students. This may be necessary for large classes.</p>       <p><strong>Step One</strong></p>       <div>        <img class=\"floatleft\" src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/transfer-grades-all-step1-V2.png\"/><ol><br/><li>In the gradebook, click the dropdown menu next to \'Final Adusted Grade\' cell.</li>          <li>Click \'Grade All\'.</li>       </ol><br clear=\"all\"/></div>       <p><strong>Step Two</strong></p>       <ol><li>Click the dropdown menu next to \'Final Grades\'.</li>          <li>Click, \'Transfer All\'. Each students\' final calculated grade will transfer to the \'Final Adusted Grade\' cell.</li>       </ol><img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/transfer-grades-all-step2.png\"/><p><strong>Final version of the gradebook, ready to send to Banner</strong></p>       <p>The gradebook below is complete. When you confirm that students grades are accurate, do one of the following:</p>       <ol><li>Send your grades to banner using the Grades2Banner transfer</li>  		<li>Export your grades to a spreadsheet to submit to your department</li>       </ol><img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/completed-gradebook-ready-for-banner.png\"/></div>','Enter and calculate grades','Array','publish','closed','closed','','enter-and-calculate-grades','','','2012-08-23 12:42:25','2012-08-23 12:42:25','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?page_id=10',2,'guides','',0),(66,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:25','2012-08-23 12:18:25','<div class=\"section\">              <p>By default, your gradebook will have default setting for calculating and displaying grades. You can make adjustments to the default settings using the <strong>Manage Grades area</strong>, or you can run the <strong>Grades Setup Wizard.</strong> The wizard will take you through screens where you can choose the options that best meet your needs.</p>                  <h3>Running the Grades Setup Wizard</h3>      <p>The wizard will help you in seven easy steps:</p>                <p><strong>STEP 1</strong></p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step1.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 2</strong></p>          <p>NOTE: if you want to transfer your grades to Banner, you must select to release the Adjusted Final Grade.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step2.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 3</strong></p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step3.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 4</strong></p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step4.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 5</strong></p>           <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step5.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 6</strong></p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step6.png\"/><p><strong>STEP 7</strong></p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Grades-Setup-Wizard-Step7.png\"/><p>You can change these settings at any time by running the wizard again or by using the Manage Grades area.</p>          <p>When you click <strong>Finish</strong>, the wizard will display a list of options for creating grade items and categories. NOTE: grade categories are optional. It may be best to start with grade items. Either way, be sure that you are following your course evaluation plan.</p></div>','Set up your gradebook','Array','publish','closed','closed','','set-up-your-gradebook-2','','','2012-08-23 12:42:25','2012-08-23 12:42:25','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?page_id=11',3,'guides','',0),(67,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:51','2012-08-23 12:18:51','<div class=\"section\">\r\n\r\nBelow is an example of a simple gradebook that an instructor created for a course. It contains the names of students who are enrolled in the course and columns for grades on assignments and exams that were in the course evaluation plan. Note that assignments (A1 and A2) are in a category for display and distribution purposes. The instructor can enter grades into each cell and save the changes. The gradebook will then calculate the final grade for each student and populate the ‘Final Calculated Grade’ column. The instructor can make adjustments as needed and transfer the grades to the ‘Final Adjusted Grade’ column.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/completed-gradeBook.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nBy default, a gradebook contains the ‘Final Calculated Grade’ and the ‘Final Adjusted Grade’ columns only. To create the grade items and categories, click <strong>Manage Grades.</strong> and click the <strong>New</strong> dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/initial-gradeBook-V2.png\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/initial-manage-grades.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nWhen you create new grade items and categories, they will display in the Manage Grades area. You can associate the grade item with a dropbox, a rubric, or a discussion topic and the grades tool will populate the columns automatically. The grades tool will use the grade items that you create to calculate and populate the \'Final Calculated Grade\' column.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/completed-manage-grades.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nThe <strong> Enter Grades</strong> area allows you to enter student grades in the appropriate columns. When you save your changes, the gradebook will complete the calculations and update the columns\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/enter-grades.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nGive the gradebook a try. You and your students will see great benefits!\r\n\r\n</div>','Tour the grades tool','Array','publish','closed','closed','','tour-the-grades-tool-2','','','2012-08-23 12:42:25','2012-08-23 12:42:25','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?page_id=12',0,'guides','',0),(68,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:58','2012-08-23 12:18:58','<div class=\"section\">               <p>You can send your final grades for your course from the Desire2Learn Grades tool to Banner.</p>       <p><strong>STEP 1: Prepare to transfer grades.</strong></p>       <p>Check the following three items in your gradebook before you transfer grades to Banner:</p>       <ol><li>In your Grades Settings, under Calculation Options, check that the <strong>Adjusted Final Grade</strong> is selected as the Final Grade Displayed</li>          <li>Under the Grade Calculations section, check that <strong>Automatically keep final grades updated</strong></li>          <li>Be sure that final grades are in the <strong>Adjusted Final Grade column</strong> in your gradebook</li>        </ol><br/><p><strong>STEP 2: Register for the Grades2Banner transfer</strong>       </p><ol><li>Go to the Grades2Banner widget, located on the bottom left of your Course Homepage</li>          <li>Click the Register for Transfer button located on the bottom of the Grades2Banner widget</li>          <li>After you click the Register button, the Grades2Banner widget will populate with new information. Under the Grades2Banner Checklist, there is a green check mark next to Registration letting you know that you are now registered for the Grades2Banner transfer</li>        </ol><p><strong>NOTE:</strong>If you want to enter an ABS or INC for a student, you must leave their final grade blank in Desire2Learn. Do not enter 0 or a partial grade as that is the grade that will be transferred to Banner. The grade for those students must be entered directly into banner.</p>       <p>More to follow + screen shots when I get them from Thomas</p></div>','Transfer final grades to the Banner Registration System','Array','publish','closed','closed','','transfer-final-grades-to-the-banner-registration-system','','','2012-08-23 12:42:25','2012-08-23 12:42:25','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wordpress33/?page_id=13',4,'guides','',0),(70,1,'2012-08-23 12:18:05','2012-08-23 12:18:05','<div class=\"section\">              <p>Create grade items and categories in the Manage Grades Area.</p>      <p><strong>Grade Items</strong> are mandatory items for your gradebook. They correspnd to an item in your evaluation plan such as \'Mid term exam.\'</p>      <p>Use<strong> Grade Categories</strong>  to organize your grade items and to make distribution of similar grades easier. For example, you may have five assignments, A1 through A5, under a category called \'Assignments.\' This makes it easy to distribute marks and drop assignments with the highest or lowest grade. Categories are not required. </p>  <p>The grades tool uses the value you give to grade items and grade categories to calculate final grades. Grade items that are in a category must sum to 100. Individual grade items and categories must also sum to 100. Otherwise, the Final Calculated Grade calculation will be inaccurate.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresources.waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/initial-manage-grades.png\"/><h3>Create grade items</h3>                <p><strong>STEP 1</strong></p>          <p>Choose the type of grade item that you want to create.</p>          <img src=\"http://facultyresourc